16/05/2005
LONDON, United Kingdom -- The EBRD announced on Friday (13 May) that it is extending a 10m-euro loan for construction of a wastewater treatment plant in Karlovac, central Croatia. 
The project aims to provide clean water and improve the sewer system in the area, which has a population of around 80,000. 
The government will apply for additional funding under EU pre-accession programmes. 
(EBRD Web site - 13/05/05)
